Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hebard, 1922" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1922" box="[238,574,1767,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,396,1767,1794]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">Eumecopoda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hebard, M." box="[404,574,1767,1793]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" pagination="121 - 299" refId="ref24613" refString="Hebard, M. (1922) Studies in Malayan, Melanesian and Australian Tettigoniidae (Orthoptera). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia, 74, 121 - 299." type="journal article" year="1922">Hebard, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1366,1839,1866]" box="[151,1366,1839,1866]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">
(Fastigium verticis blunt, with transverse keel; gap between fastigium frontis and fastigium distinct; 
<figureCitation box="[1277,1358,1839,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,687,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-253@29.[151,1436,687,1762]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 16. Frontal view of the head in Mecopoda and Eumecopoda species. A M. angusta, male, B M. angusta, female, C M. dilatata, male, syntype, D M. divergens, male, NMW, E M. divergens, female, holotype, F E. cyrtoscelis zhantievi subsp. nov., male, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141318" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141318/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="132" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,644,1936,1963]" box="[151,644,1936,1963]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis box="[151,330,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">Paramecopoda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[338,524,1936,1963]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" pagination="564 - 586" refId="ref24348" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2020) A review of the genus Mecopoda (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Mecopodinae) from Indo-Malayan and Papuan Regions. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute RAS, 324 (4), 564 - 586. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / trudyzin / 2020.324.4.564" type="journal article" year="2020">Gorochov 2020</bibRefCitation>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[536,644,1937,1963]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">syn. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,2003,2030]" lastBlockId="31.[151,1437,151,933]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="132" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1922" box="[273,419,2003,2029]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[273,419,2003,2029]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">Eumecopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hebard, M." box="[636,800,2003,2029]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" pagination="121 - 299" refId="ref24613" refString="Hebard, M. (1922) Studies in Malayan, Melanesian and Australian Tettigoniidae (Orthoptera). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia, 74, 121 - 299." type="journal article" year="1922">Hebard (1922)</bibRefCitation>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Karsch, 1888" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1888" box="[863,1168,2003,2029]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrtoscelis">
<emphasis box="[863,1013,2003,2029]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">E. cyrtoscelis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Karsch, F." box="[1020,1168,2003,2029]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" pagination="145 - 148" refId="ref25123" refString="Karsch, F. (1888) Zwei neue Mecopoda - Arten (Orthoptera). Entomologische Nachrichten, Berlin, 14, 145 - 148." type="journal article" year="1888">Karsch, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[1205,1253,2004,2030]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">type</typeStatus>
species. Hebard listed several supposed genus-specific characters. However, not all of them are diagnostic. Interestingly, the shape of the fastigium is described as looking as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Redtenbacher" authorityYear="1892" box="[663,788,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilatata">
<emphasis box="[663,788,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">M. dilatata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[844,990,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[844,990,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">M. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but Hebard did not mention these species. Also with regard to the distinct gap between fastigium frontis and fastigium verticis 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1888" box="[1147,1298,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrtoscelis">
<emphasis box="[1147,1298,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">E. cyrtoscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to these species (
<figureCitation box="[311,394,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,687,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-253@29.[151,1436,687,1762]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 16. Frontal view of the head in Mecopoda and Eumecopoda species. A M. angusta, male, B M. angusta, female, C M. dilatata, male, syntype, D M. divergens, male, NMW, E M. divergens, female, holotype, F E. cyrtoscelis zhantievi subsp. nov., male, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141318" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141318/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1922" box="[444,590,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[444,590,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">Eumecopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Hebard, M." box="[743,906,259,285]" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" pagination="121 - 299" refId="ref24613" refString="Hebard, M. (1922) Studies in Malayan, Melanesian and Australian Tettigoniidae (Orthoptera). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia, 74, 121 - 299." type="journal article" year="1922">Hebard (1922)</bibRefCitation>
„the tips of the tegmina are somewhat falcate“. This characteristic, however, is also seen in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heller &amp; Baker &amp; Ingrisch &amp; Korsunovskaya &amp; Liu &amp; Riede &amp; Warchałowska-Šliwa" authorityYear="2021" box="[664,829,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyphoea">
<emphasis box="[664,829,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">M. platyphoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[847,934,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[217,1404,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-27@32.[184,1404,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 19. Tegmina in Mecopoda and Eumecopoda species. A M. angusta, male, B M. angusta, female, C M. divergens, female, holotype, photo without scale, size according to the description, D E. platyphoea stat. nov., female, holotype, E E. cyrtoscelis zhantievi subsp. nov., male, holotype, F E. cyrtoscelis zhantievi subsp. nov., female, paratype. Scale 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141324/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Hebard mentions also the structure of the tympana in the fore tibiae, open in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1831" box="[546,664,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[546,664,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">Mecopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and partially closed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1922" box="[928,1074,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[928,1074,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">Eumecopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Griffini, A." pageId="31" pageNumber="132" pagination="271 - 288" refId="ref24302" refString="Griffini, A. (1908) Sopra alcuni Stenopelmatidi e sopra alcune Mecopodidi Malesi ed Austro-Malesi. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 46, 271 - 288. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 9961" type="journal article" year="1908">Griffini (1908)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1888" box="[241,394,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrtoscelis">
<emphasis box="[241,394,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">E. cyrtoscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
„has considerable variability in the structure of the tympani of the front tibiae, now almost concave, now rhymed, often differently made to the front side and the back side, being able to be in the open side and in this somewhat closed or even vice versa“ (
<bibRefCitation author="Griffini, A." box="[696,848,439,465]" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" pagination="271 - 288" refId="ref24302" refString="Griffini, A. (1908) Sopra alcuni Stenopelmatidi e sopra alcune Mecopodidi Malesi ed Austro-Malesi. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 46, 271 - 288. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 9961" type="journal article" year="1908">Griffini 1908</bibRefCitation>
, translated). A similar or even larger variation is seen in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Redtenbacher" authorityYear="1892" box="[179,302,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilatata">
<emphasis box="[179,302,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">M. dilatata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where specimens with open tympana and with the condition as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1888" box="[1041,1191,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrtoscelis">
<emphasis box="[1041,1191,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">E. cyrtoscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been found (
<bibRefCitation author="Fritze, A." pageId="31" pageNumber="132" pagination="335 - 340" refId="ref24243" refString="Fritze, A. (1900) Orthopteres de l' Archipel Malais. (Voyage de MM. M. Bedot et C. Pictet dans l' Archipel Malais). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 7 (1899), 335 - 340. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 32949" type="journal article" year="1900">Fritze 1900</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Griffini, A." box="[263,416,511,537]" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" pagination="271 - 288" refId="ref24302" refString="Griffini, A. (1908) Sopra alcuni Stenopelmatidi e sopra alcune Mecopodidi Malesi ed Austro-Malesi. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 46, 271 - 288. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 9961" type="journal article" year="1908">Griffini 1908</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[436,631,511,537]" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" pagination="564 - 586" refId="ref24348" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2020) A review of the genus Mecopoda (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Mecopodinae) from Indo-Malayan and Papuan Regions. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute RAS, 324 (4), 564 - 586. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / trudyzin / 2020.324.4.564" type="journal article" year="2020">Gorochov (2020)</bibRefCitation>
used this character to differentiate his new (sub)genus 
<emphasis box="[1258,1437,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">Paramecopoda.</emphasis>
All 
<taxonomicName box="[193,426,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[193,339,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">Eumecopoda</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(no information available for 
<emphasis box="[760,883,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1891" box="[760,875,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walkeri">E. walkeri</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
seem to have femora supplied dorsally with blunt tubercles, a characteristic not found outside the genus and also not found in 
<emphasis box="[997,1288,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">
Paramecopoda 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heller &amp; Baker &amp; Ingrisch &amp; Korsunovskaya &amp; Liu &amp; Riede &amp; Warchałowska-Šliwa" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Gorochov" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1174,1288,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosa">granulosa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(no information available for 
<emphasis box="[349,528,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heller &amp; Baker &amp; Ingrisch &amp; Korsunovskaya &amp; Liu &amp; Riede &amp; Warchałowska-Šliwa" authorityYear="2021" box="[349,516,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyphoea">M. platyphoea</taxonomicName>
).
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">
We will use the character from 
<bibRefCitation author="Hebard, M." box="[556,739,655,681]" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" pagination="121 - 299" refId="ref24613" refString="Hebard, M. (1922) Studies in Malayan, Melanesian and Australian Tettigoniidae (Orthoptera). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia, 74, 121 - 299." type="journal article" year="1922">Hebard’s (1922)</bibRefCitation>
description „the tips of the tegmina are somewhat falcate“ as differential character of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1922" box="[426,572,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eumecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[426,572,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="132">Eumecopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
